metadata.name: NEUROMANCER
metadata.description: Neuromancer is a piece that captures the interaction of human+machine and how it can become a  metal prison that can alter our brain's  ego. The artwork is also a wink to the  1984 science fiction novel by American-Canadian writer William Gibson : "Neuromancer" which is known to be one of the pioneers of the cyberpunk genre, the first book to jot down the term  "cyberspace" and the one who brought the idea of a metaverse (digital world) to the mainstream culture...an underrated staple of our. culture and our community...
